        {
          "text": "Gascia Ouzounian, “Rethinking Acoustic Ecology: Sound Art and Environment,” "
        },
        {
          "text": "Evental Aesthetics",
          "italic": true
        },
        {
          "text": ", 6:1, 2017. This essay challenges romantic ideas about “nature sound” and reframes acoustic ecology as shaped by mediation, power, and politics. Ouzounian gives us language to hear ice, flood, and plant sounds as systems that are recorded, circulated, and governed. "
        }
